cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about facial landmark tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new approach to solving the least squares problem, which involves machine learning techniques such as functional regression and cascaded regression. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also involves image and video processing, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a fast approach for incremental learning, which involves optimization techniques such as stochastic gradient descent, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
